{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Sufism","audienceTags":["tradition:sufism","tradition:islam","theme:love","audience:meditation"],"sortPriority":32,"groupingLevels":[],"groupingLabels":[],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Rabia_AlAdawiyya.json","supplementalDataPath":null,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"devotional","sourceId":"rabiaAlAdawiyya","displayName":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","version":"1.0","language":"English","edition":"Public Domain Translations","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","itemCount":11,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true},"data":[{"id":"rabia-ext-000001","text":"I so detached my heart from the world and cut short my hopes that for thirty years now I have performed each prayer as though it were my last and I were praying the prayer of farewell.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000002","text":"O God! If I worship You for fear of Hell, burn me in Hell","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000003","text":"I want to put out the fires of Hell, and burn down the rewards of Paradise. They block the way to Allah. I do not want to worship from fear of punishment or for the promise of reward, but simply for the love of Allah.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:islam","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000004","text":"Love, for Rabia, is the basis of spiritual perfection at all the stages on the journey to God. She teaches to love God for the sake of God.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000005","text":"O my Lord! If I worship Thee on account of the fear of Hell, burn me in Hell, and if I worship Thee with the hope of Paradise, exclude me from it, but if I worship Thee for Thine own sake, then withhold not from me Thine Eternal Beauty.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000006","text":"I have not served God for fear of Hell, for I should be like a wretched hireling, If I did it for fear: nor for love of Paradise, for I should be a bad servant if I served for the sake of what was given, but I have served Him only for the love of Him and out of desire for Him.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000007","text":"Repentance is attained by the saints with the Divine grace and it comes from the side of God who enlightens the hearts of those whom He loves. Seeking a formal forgiveness is the sin for lying. If I seek repentance of my self, I shall have need of repentance again.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000008","text":"Seclusion is the soul's ideal preparation for reaching God. It is in the state of solitude that the soul contemplates on the attributes of God.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000009","text":"The soul comes from God and it can be united with Him if it is purified through the process of mortification.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000010","text":"Were Women all like those whom here I name,Woman to man I surely would prefer;The Sun is feminine, nor deems it shame;The Moon, though masculine, depends on her.","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"rabia-ext-000011","text":"[https:/6277-6012-8508-1640/archive.org/details/the-sayings-and-teachings-of-the-great-mystics-of-islam-2004/page/31/mode/2up Mohammed Riaz Qadiri: \"'The Sayings and Teachings of the Great Mystics of Islam's, Gujranwala, پاکستان، ۲۰۰۴","author":"Rabia al-Adawiyya","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:islam","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."}]}